  rdfs:label """The author provides lots of hints in his writing to give the reader clues and help them form predictions about the plot."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.604746Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7183-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Lila wants to be a firework-maker and discover the secret to it but her father Lalchand wants her to find a husband."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.604754Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7183-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Lila's friend Chulak speaks to Lalchand and finds out the secret ingredient for firework-making and where to find it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.604762Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7826-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Marcy and the Riddle of the Sphinx' contains important themes relevant to traditional myths and modern life experiences"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.605946Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7826-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea, topic of message that recurs in a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.605954Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7826-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Marcy displays courage, integrity and resilience, among other qualities, in her quest."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.605969Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7826-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Readers can interpret a text, its themes and its meaning in different ways."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.605977Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7826-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Discussing books with others can deepen our understanding and allow us to develop our own views."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.605985Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7188-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Oral rehearsal of a recount ensures we have a clear understanding of the chronology of events."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608320Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7188-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When rehearsing and planning for a diary entry, we do so in the first person from the character's perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608328Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7188-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An effective plan for a diary entry contains key events in chronological order and thoughts/feelings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608335Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7188-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A plan is written in note format using bullet points to capture the most important information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608342Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7188-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Lila's first diary entry will recount her day making fireworks and discovering her father's views on her future."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608350Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4897-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Information in the adaptations section is specific for the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608915Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4897-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Text cohesion refers to how a piece of writing flows, engages the reader and achieves its purpose."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4897-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Brackets can be used for parenthesis."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608930Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4897-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Planning is an essential part of the writing process."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608937Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4897-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Plans should include notes, bullet points and initial ideas that can be developed further when writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.608944Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7184-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using inference can help us to draw greater conclusions about Lila and Lalchand's relationship."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609512Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7184-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The relationship between Lila and Lalchand is central to the plot."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609519Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7184-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Lila and Lalchand have conflicting views on her future."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609527Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7184-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Lalchand's views are stereotypical of traditional ideas around the role that girls and women should play."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609534Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7184-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Lila's desires challenge stereotypes for girls and she defies her father in pursuit of her dreams."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609541Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1303-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adding the suffix -ed turns the verb into the past tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609938Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1303-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When the vowel sound is long, we just add the suffix -ed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609945Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1303-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When the vowel sound is short, we double the consonant and add the suffix -ed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609952Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1303-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell irregular verbs in the past tense, such as slept."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609959Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1303-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: different, material and busy."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.609966Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7185-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The protagonist is a main character or central figure in a story or narrative."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610353Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7185-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Lila is the protagonist in the story 'The Firework Maker's Daughter'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610360Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7185-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Character development builds a unique character with depth, personality and motivations that the reader can connect to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610367Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7185-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can identify Lila's character traits by exploring her experiences and interactions and making inferences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610375Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7185-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Lila displays a range of character traits such as resilience, determination and courage."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8466-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Oral rehearsal of a recount ensures we have a clear understanding of the chronology of events."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610925Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8466-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When rehearsing and planning for a diary entry, we do so in the first person from the character's perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8466-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An effective plan for a diary entry contains key events in chronological order and thoughts/feelings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610944Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8466-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A plan is written in note format using bullet points to capture the most important information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610951Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8466-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Lila's second diary entry will recount her discovering her father's betrayal and her decision to leave on her quest."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.610958Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

