oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5657-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To be successful, the team tested for many years, until the rover was ready to launch on the 26th November 2011."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623644Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7871-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Greenling' is a picturebook text; it can be considered to be a fable."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623813Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7871-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fables usually explain the creation of the world, natural events and the origins of rituals or customs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623819Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7871-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Words can have multiple meanings; pupils can explore these through a 'word explosion'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623824Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7871-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In ‘Greenling’, vignettes offer glimpses into specific moments or aspects of the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623832Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7871-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Greenling has a positive effect on the Barleycorns and their local community."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623838Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7909-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The migration of people from the Caribbean to the UK during the Windrush period was driven by a combination of factors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623876Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7909-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The song is written from the perspective of someone who had been to London even though Roberts had not yet visited."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7909-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To determine the purpose and audience of a song, we can consider the music and lyrics of the song."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623886Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7909-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose & audience of songs can change over time; when the context of a song changes, so can its purpose & audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623892Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6110-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Information can be gathered from a range of different sources."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623897Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6110-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Credibility of each source must be determined."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623903Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6110-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Origin of a source must be cited."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623908Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6110-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Full sentences are not required when writing in note form."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623913Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6110-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Notes can be organised by theme using bullet points."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623918Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28400-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Characterisation is the way an author & illustrator describe & develop the personalities & traits of the characters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623973Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28400-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Role on the wall' is a reading activity that helps readers develop their understanding of a character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28400-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """“The Beast” refers to Nate’s internal struggle with anger and frustration, which he can sometimes struggle to control."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623984Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28400-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Characters can change and develop throughout a narrative and traits they show do not always remain fixed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6379-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reciting a text provides an important opportunity for developing speaking and listening skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.623995Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6379-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Speakers need to consider how to keep their audience engaged during a recital."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624000Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6379-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Speakers can use a range of techniques to ensure that they can be clearly heard and are engaging for the audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624005Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6379-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Memorising a text can enable a more coherent recital."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624011Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6379-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use a range of strategies to support us with memorising a text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5487-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘Escape from Pompeii’ is written from the perspective of Tranio, a young boy."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624021Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5487-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Characterisation can change over the course of a text’s narrative."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624027Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5487-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Characterisation can be conveyed through a character’s appearance, their dialogue and actions they perform in the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624032Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6518-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The passengers of the Empire Windrush were seeking better job opportunities and a new life in Britain."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624040Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6518-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Windrush passengers were mostly men, many of whom had served in the British Armed Forces during the Second World War."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624046Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6518-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Some Britons welcomed the Windrush Generation as a much-needed source of labour while others opposed their arrival."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624051Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6518-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The 1958 Notting Hill Race Riots damaged trust between the Afro-Caribbean community and the British establishment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624056Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6518-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Despite the significant challenges they faced, the Windrush Generation made extensive contributions to British society."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624061Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5759-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Understanding the context of a text enables readers to engage effectively with the content."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624123Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5759-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The author is the person who wrote the text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624129Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5759-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The illustrator is the person who illustrated the text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624134Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5759-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fiction is literature in the form of prose that describes imaginary events and people."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624141Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7904-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Characterisation is the way an author and illustrator develop the personalities and traits of the characters in a story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624149Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7904-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Authors and illustrators use a range of methods to convey characterisation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624155Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7904-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Stereotypes can often be found in traditional fairy tales."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624161Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7904-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Stereotypes can include assumptions based on gender, age and culture."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624166Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7904-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Blackberry Blue’ addresses and challenges stereotypes through its storytelling and characterisation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624171Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6099-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Information can be gathered from a range of different sources."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624177Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6099-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Credibility of each source must be determined."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624182Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6099-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Origin of a source must be cited."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624188Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6099-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Full sentences are not required when writing in note form."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624193Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6099-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Notes can be organised by theme using bullet points."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624198Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6119-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Publishing our work is the final stage of the writing process where we prepare our writing ready for an audience to see."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624225Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6119-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Published work should be written in clear, joined handwriting with letters that start on the line."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624230Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6119-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A published non-chronological report will usually include a picture or diagram."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624235Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6119-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We indent each new paragraph and underline subheadings with a ruler and we follow any appropriate layout conventions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624244Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6342-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when it is planned."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624385Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6342-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Vocabulary can be planned to precisely match a setting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624391Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6342-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can mention items from the appropriate time period in order to show the historical context of a setting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624396Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6342-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can use fronted adverbials and preposition phrases to show where items are in a setting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624401Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7905-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The new Queen is poisoning Prince Just. Blackberry Blue cures him and he reappears at the climax of the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624407Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7905-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Readers can infer by using clues from within the text to draw conclusions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624412Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7905-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Evidence from the text can be used to develop answers to questions and support reasoning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624417Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7905-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Evidence should be concise and justify the point that readers are trying to make in relation to the question."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624422Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7905-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An impression of a person, place or thing can be formed by a reader's initial feelings or from prior experience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624430Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7928-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The weather in Trinidad contrasted between being hot and raining."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624436Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7928-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Imagery in writing refers to the use of vivid and descriptive language that appeals to the senses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624441Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7928-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Imagery is used by the author, Floella Benjamin, during Chapter 4 to convey how she experiences her childhood setting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624446Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8077-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reader identity is the process of reflecting on what you enjoy or do not enjoy reading"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624455Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8077-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading is a very personal experience; it is unique to every reader"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624460Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8077-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading can take many forms; it does not have to be restricted to a book"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624466Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8077-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Texts can connect with readers on an emotional and intellectual level"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8077-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Texts can have a profound effect on the reader"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624476Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5485-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connecting information in "Escape from Pompeii" to our background knowledge can help us to deepen our understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624481Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5485-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Before the eruption of Mount Vesuvius, Pompeii was a busy Roman city."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624487Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5485-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Mount Vesuvius erupted on 24 August AD 79."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624492Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5485-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The city was covered in ash and many people died."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624497Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5485-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The afterword provides the reader with valuable information and context."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624503Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5763-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the opening is to engage the reader and introduce characters and plot."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5763-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using a range of linguistic devices helps achieve text purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624516Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5763-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A non-finite complex sentence is formed of a main clause and a non-finite subordinate clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624521Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7911-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Sweet Jamaica' was written by Lord Kitchener in London, 1952, four years after his arrival on HMT Empire Windrush."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624543Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7911-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Sweet Jamaica’ shows a change in perspective from Lord Kitchener, after he had spent time in London."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624548Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7911-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The song creates negative imagery in its lyrics, portraying themes of regret, nostalgia and homesickness."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624556Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7911-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By exploring the context, themes and perspectives, we can gain a better understanding of the song."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624562Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28385-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Doing Nothing’ is a poem found in the poetry collection, ‘Dear Ugly Sisters’ by Laura Mucha."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624622Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28385-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The poem is about the practice of mindfulness and the rhythm varies in the poem to reflect the atmosphere."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624627Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28385-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘Travel by Book’ is is a fixed verse poem, which follows the AAAB rhyme scheme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624632Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28385-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The poem has a clear, steady rhythm, which gives the poem a flowing and musical quality."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624638Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28385-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Doing deep breaths before performing can help us to feel calm and reduce nerves."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624644Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8894-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘How to Train Your Dragon’ is an illustrated chapter book."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624725Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8894-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The text draws influences from Viking history, Norse mythology and folklore."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624730Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8894-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The text references the notion of being a hero."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624736Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8894-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Understanding the context of the story can help readers build connections and deepen understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8464-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reading aloud involves using an expressive voice, varying volume, emphasising keywords and using facial expressions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624746Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8464-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Roald Dahl uses repetition, ambiguity and a cliffhanger to create a scary atmosphere in the opening chapter."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624752Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8464-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Inferring is about drawing conclusions or making educated guesses based on information and clues provided in a text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624757Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8464-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Evidence from the text is used to support inferences we make about a character or an event in a text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624762Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8464-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Precise vocabulary choices, setting descriptions and purposeful sentence structures are used to build suspense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624767Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6412-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Britain had a vast empire in the early 20th Century, but it was very badly affected by WWII and had labour shortages."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624802Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6412-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In 1948, a new law clarified that all citizens of the Commonwealth had the right to settle and work in the UK."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624808Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6412-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There was high unemployment in the Caribbean; many people hoped for better wages and living conditions in the UK."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624813Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6412-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """West Indian immigrants therefore arrived in Britain on ships including the Empire Windrush at this time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624818Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6412-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "On arrival, they faced discrimination in jobs, services and housing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624824Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8080-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """looking at picture books that deal with complex themes can develop an understanding of the wider world"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624829Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8080-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """a verse novel is a type of narrative poetry in which a novel length narrative is told through the medium of poetry"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624835Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8080-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """a picture book has meaning that can be constructed from text, image or an interplay between both"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624840Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8080-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """greater meaning can be elicited from a text by reflecting on the author or illustrator's specific choice of word/image"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624845Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8078-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Texts can be adapted into a television series, feature-length film or for a theatre performance"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624850Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8078-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A character can be imagined from a physical text, film, television adaptation or theatre performance"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624856Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8078-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Subtext and themes can be explored via a character's thoughts, actions, dialogue and character development"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624861Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6216-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Before we write an essay, we need to research the subject, making notes that include subject-specific vocabulary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624866Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6216-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The Amazon rainforest is a vast and special habitat with huge biodiversity."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624874Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6216-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The Amazon rainforest is being subject to deforestation driven by agriculture."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6216-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This deforestation contributes to climate change because trees are carbon stores."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4891-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Research into a subject improves the writing of a non-chronological report about it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624929Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4891-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Aye-ayes are nocturnal, highly-adapted mammals that live in the tropical rainforests of Madagascar, Africa."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624935Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4891-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adaptations are features that animals and plants have to help them survive in their environments."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4891-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Aye-ayes’ adaptations enable them to find and eat food."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624946Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4891-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Aye-ayes’ diets consist of grubs, fruit, nectar and nuts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624951Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7873-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are many themes that are explored in ‘Greenling’ including change and transformation, sustainability & rewilding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.624998Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7873-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reading around a text can deepen our understanding of significant themes and ideas in a text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625003Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7873-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sharing personal responses allows readers to engage more deeply with the story and build connections to the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625008Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7873-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Different readers may interpret a text in different ways."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5761-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The setting description describes where the narrative takes place."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625024Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5761-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adverbial detail describes when, where or how things happened."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625031Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5761-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Ambitious, precise verbs and descriptive adjectives help the reader visualise the scene."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625036Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5761-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using a range of sentence types enhances text cohesion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625041Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6111-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Information can be gathered from a range of different sources."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625047Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6111-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Credibility of each source must be determined."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625052Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6111-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Origin of a source must be cited."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625057Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6111-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Full sentences are not required when writing in note form."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625063Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6111-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Notes can be organised by theme using bullet points."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625068Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8079-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Making a text recommendation includes a personal reason for why the text was relevant to you"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625073Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8079-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Making a text recommendation includes a reason that someone else might enjoy the text"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625079Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8079-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You can read books written by a range of authors/illustrators to learn about different cultures and perspectives"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625084Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8079-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You can read books in any language that you understand and share these with peers or family"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625089Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4847-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Information can be gathered from a range of different sources (both primary and secondary)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625146Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4847-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Journalists research the topic of their reports in order to write accurately about the topic."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625151Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4847-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When conducting initial research, facts can be kept general."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625157Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6391-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Poems can be learned by heart and recited."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6391-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Understanding of the poem's meaning can be shown through intonation, tone, volume and action."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625229Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6391-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Clear diction is essential for the audience to understand the words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625235Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6391-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using a range of recital skills can enhance our performance and audience engagement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625240Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6391-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Eye contact is an important aspect of public speaking."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625246Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7913-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Girl of Ink and Stars’ is a novel, which blends the genres of myth and magical realism."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625316Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7913-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The text has strong links to location and navigation; maps are a central part of the narrative."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625321Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7913-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In 'The Girl of Ink and Stars', the themes of sacrifice, friendship and redemption are explored."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625330Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7913-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Different readers may interpret a text in different ways."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625335Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6718-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Charles Darwin was a British naturalist known for his contributions to the theory of evolution."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625341Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6718-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A biography is a non-fiction text so we must do research to gather factual information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625346Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6718-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A text map can be used to help us learn and remember the key events of someone's life."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625352Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6718-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In the text map, pictures represent key events (and a few words and numbers can be used too)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625357Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6718-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The more we rehearse a text map out loud, the better we will remember it."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625362Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7930-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Turning points in a text mark the change in direction for a character; this effects the plot."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625368Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7930-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Significant moments in the text can be both positive or negative."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625373Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7930-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Turning points can evoke a range of emotions in characters."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625378Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28949-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Poets can use a range of poetic devices to enhance the meaning or impact of their poems."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625400Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28949-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Alliteration is when words that begin with the same sound are placed close together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625405Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28949-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Onomtopoeia refers to words that imitate the natural sounds associated with the objects or actions they refer to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625411Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28949-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Understanding a poem, its language and the impression it creates will help us to create an impactful performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625416Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28949-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are many things we can do to prepare for a performance, including practising reading the poem aloud."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625421Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28386-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In the poem ‘I’m an Orchestra’, Laura Mucha compares the emotional life of a human to an orchestra."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28386-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Poets might use devices such as repetition, rhyme or alliteration to enhance the sound of the poem read aloud."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625485Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28386-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A metaphor is a way of describing something by saying that it is something else."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625491Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28386-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Alliteration is when words that begin with the same sound are placed close together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625499Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28386-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Marking up a poem for performance involves adding notes to guide delivery, emphasising elements like tone & pace."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625505Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7903-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Blackberry Blue’ is a collection of six fairy tales, with characters from various backgrounds and cultures."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625510Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7903-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Each tale contains magical elements and fantastical occurrences, which is a key feature of the genre."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625515Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7903-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Blackberry Blue' leans on traditional fairy tales for inspiration."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625520Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7903-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The theme of good and evil is explored in 'Blackberry Blue'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625525Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7903-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Blackberry Blue' begins with a prologue: a paragraph that sets the stage for the fairy tale that is about to follow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625530Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8009-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Joseph Coelho is a British poet and children’s author."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625535Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8009-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Joseph Coelho is known for using engaging and emotive themes in his poetry, such as identity, family and friendship."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625540Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8009-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In 2014, he had his very first poetry collection published called ‘Werewolf Club Rules’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625545Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8009-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """He was appointed Children’s Laureate in 2022 to celebrate his exceptional talent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625553Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8088-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘No. 115 Dreams’ is a free verse poem; it contains five verses and a repeated refrain."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625558Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8088-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘No. 115 Dreams’ contains several examples of personification."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625563Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8088-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Rooms and objects are describing family members or events that occurred in the house."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625568Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8088-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A poem can have multiple meanings and interpretations; each person’s response can be different and unique to them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625574Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8088-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can respond to a poem by writing a personal response to it."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8090-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When writing a poem about a place, it’s important to paint a vivid picture of the setting through our description."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625609Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8090-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sensory description can be used to help the reader visualise the place being written about."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625617Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8090-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Imagery we create can convey an atmosphere."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625622Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8090-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use poems that we have studied to inspire us in our own poem."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625627Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8090-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using enjambment in our poems can enhance the flow of the poem, engaging the reader or listener."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625632Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8082-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Imagery refers to the use of language that evokes vivid mental pictures in the reader's mind."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625638Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8082-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In the poem 'London', William Blake uses sensory language to paint a vivid image."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625643Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8082-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sounds are important in the poem, such as the "infant's cry of fear" and the "chimney-sweeper's cry"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625650Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8082-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The use of negative sounds in the poem creates a noisy and unpleasant impression of the city."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625655Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8082-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Different kinds of language have different effects."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625661Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8085-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing about the impact of a poem allows for a deeper analysis of its effectiveness."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625668Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8085-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are certain poetry conventions that we can include in our writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8085-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Poetry conventions include naming the poet and title of the poem, using quotes and referring to the context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8085-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When writing about the impact of a poem we can discuss the poet, the poem’s imagery and structure, and the context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625684Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8089-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Tempest Avenue’ can be described as a free verse poem; it contains 7 verses and is written in first person perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625689Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8089-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Tempest Avenue' is set in Stairfoot, Yorkshire; it is written from the perspective of a parent holding their baby."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625694Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8089-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The poem uses enjambment, which is when a line in poetry continues onto the next line without pause or punctuation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625699Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8089-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Understanding a poem, its language and the impression it creates will help us to create an impactful performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625705Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8084-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """After we have taken time to understand a poem’s meaning, themes and structure, we can learn a poem off by heart."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625710Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8084-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Learning poetry by heart offers a range of benefits, both emotionally and academically."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625715Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8084-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Hiding certain words in a poem engages readers in active retrieval practice, strengthening our memory recall."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625721Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8084-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Understanding a poem, its language and the impression it creates will help us to create an impactful performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625726Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8084-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can improve our performances by considering the pace, the atmosphere and our own use of voice and movement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625731Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8081-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'London' was published in 1794."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625736Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8081-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """William Blake was an English poet and artist who believed in social and racial equality."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8081-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In the poem, the narrator is describing a walk around the city of London."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8081-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Romanticism was a movement in art and literature."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625755Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8081-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Romantic poets were often critical of industrialisation and valued the simplicity and purity of rural life."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625760Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8083-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The poem is a dramatic monologue; this is when one person speaks in a poem or story, sharing their perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625801Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8083-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The poem has a structured form with a consistent rhyme scheme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625806Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8083-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The poem has an ABAB rhyme scheme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625811Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8083-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Blake uses repetition to emphasise certain words or phrases or to create a particular effect."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625817Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8083-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reader's viewpoints about the impact of the poem may differ as we are all unique."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625822Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28947-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A poet uses language to express ideas, thoughts and feelings in a creative way."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625962Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28947-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Joseph Coelho is a British poet and children’s author, who was appointed Children’s Laureate in 2022."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625967Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28947-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Joseph Coelho is known for using engaging and emotive themes in his poetry, such as identity, family and friendship."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625972Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28947-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The poem 'Story Builders' reflects on the process of building a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625978Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28947-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When reading a poem, we can use our voice and tone to create an impression on the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.625983Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5805-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Romeo and Juliet' is a tragedy written by William Shakespeare in the 1590s and it is based on an Italian story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626066Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5805-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The plot tells of two young lovers, Romeo Montague and Juliet Capulet, who belong to feuding families."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626071Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5805-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theme of a play is a central idea that the writer intends the audience to engage deeply with."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626076Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5805-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Key themes in 'Romeo and Juliet' are love, chance, conflict, youth and death."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626081Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1061-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The purpose of the introduction is to give general information to the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626087Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1061-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The introduction outlines what the reader will learn from the non-chronological report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626092Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1061-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The facts in the introduction are general facts about the Stone Age; they become more specific in later paragraphs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626097Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1061-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An introduction ends with a command to the reader to continue reading."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626102Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1061-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Viewpoint fronted adverbials can be useful to introduce a fact."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626107Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7919-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When we read texts, we connect them to our own experiences and to 'big ideas'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626509Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7919-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can identify these 'big ideas' using concepts and themes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626514Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7919-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Readers may interpret texts differently based on their reading of the material or their own experiences and beliefs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626519Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7919-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can support our views about concepts and themes linked to a text by providing evidence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626524Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6759-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of an essay can be to present a coherent argument in response to a question or statement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626529Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6759-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To meet its purpose effectively, the tone of an essay must be formal and informative."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626534Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6759-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using correct linguistic features of an essay enables writers to meet the text's purpose."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626540Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7663-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of direct speech in a narrative is to develop characters and advance the plot."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626545Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7663-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using a range of sentence types (simple, compound and complex) improves text flow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626550Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7663-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Fronted adverbials of time, place or manner add extra detail to a main clause."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626555Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7663-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This narrative version of 'Whale Rider' is written in the past tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626560Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7663-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Oral rehearsal before writing helps to structure grammatically correct sentences and check for sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.626568Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6742-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Those executed or accused of witchcraft in Early Modern Scotland would often have been vulnerable people."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627059Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6742-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use role play and drama to try and empathise with these characters."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627066Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6742-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We also need to consider the motivations of their accusers."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627072Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6742-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We should aim to remember that these were real people who suffered real persecution."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627077Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5823-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the build-up is to develop the plot and characters, introduce a problem and start to build up tension."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627171Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5823-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Internal thoughts are the thoughts, ideas, or questions that occur within an individual's mind."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627176Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5823-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Internal thoughts are written using the same sentence structure as reported speech."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627184Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5823-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """These are important to include in our writing because they tell the reader what a character is thinking/feeling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627190Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6343-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when it is planned."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627430Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6343-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Setting descriptions can start from a bird's eye view and zoom in to a city's streets."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627435Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6343-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We use adjectives and rich vocabulary and we explore the five senses to set a particular mood when describing a setting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6343-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Fronted adverbials of place and preposition phrases place items in a setting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627445Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6343-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can write a setting description in the third person and the present tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.627450Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6344-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when structure, content and vocabulary is planned."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628023Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6344-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Oral rehearsal is an important step in the writing process."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628028Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6344-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of place, prepositions and precise vocabulary paint the picture for a reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628033Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6344-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Complex sentences can be used to show the connections between ideas."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628038Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6344-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can show the historical context of our setting by referring to items from the time period."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628043Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5474-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea, topic or message that recurs within a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628087Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5474-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Readers can interpret the importance of themes, ideas and messages differently."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628094Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5474-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Hansel and Gretel' explores a variety of themes linked to morality."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628099Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5474-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Analysing themes can help us consider human morality and positively impact the people we want to be."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628104Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6100-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Information can be gathered from a range of different sources."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6100-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Credibility of each source must be determined."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628114Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6100-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Origin of a source must be cited."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628119Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6100-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Established facts and relevant evidence can be used to strengthen the writer's position on a subject."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628124Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6100-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Relevant statistics can enhance the evidence cited."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628129Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28383-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Poets can use a range of poetic devices to enhance the meaning or impact of their poems."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628158Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28383-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Personification is describing a non-living thing as if it is a person."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628163Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28383-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Alliteration is when words that begin with the same sound are placed close together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28383-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Understanding a poem, its language and the impression it creates will help us to create an impactful performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628175Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28383-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are many things we can do to prepare for a performance, including practising reading the poem aloud."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628180Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2743-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A modal verb is a type of auxiliary verb."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628239Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2743-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A modal verb is most often paired with the main verb of a clause."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628244Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2743-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A modal verb is not paired with the main verb if it appears in a question."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628249Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2743-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Modal verbs are often used in speech sentences and persuasive writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628254Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2743-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A modal verb expresses the degree of possibility, intent, ability or necessity of the clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.628258Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28382-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A poet uses language to express ideas, thoughts and feelings in a creative way."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629235Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28382-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Laura Mucha is an English writer and award-winning poet."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629240Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28382-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘Dear Ugly Sisters’ is Laura Mucha’s debut poetry collection for children."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629244Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28382-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The poem ‘Dear Ugly Sisters’ is presented as a goodbye letter from Cinderella to the ugly sisters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629249Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7647-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Expressing the thoughts and emotions of a character helps the reader understand the character more."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629519Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7647-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Different character traits appear in the story and we use these to draw conclusions to infer a moral from the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629523Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7647-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A moral is a lesson that can be learnt from a story; readers’ interpretations of a moral may differ."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7647-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The characters’ emotions change throughout the narrative."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629533Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7647-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can look at each character's speech and actions to understand their emotions fully."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629538Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7646-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The Happy Prince' is a story originally written in 1888 by Oscar Wilde, which has been adapted into different versions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629925Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7646-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The story tells of a statue of a prince witnessing great poverty and sadness in a city."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629930Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7646-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Together with a swallow, the prince performs selfless acts of kindness to help the poor people of the city."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629935Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7646-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The moral of the story in ‘The Happy Prince’ is to be compassionate and to help those who are suffering."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7646-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Summarising the key events in a story helps us to build our understanding of the text and the meaning behind it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629944Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3402-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A subheading signals to the reader what the section is about."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629973Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3402-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Careful selection of nouns and pronouns ensures cohesion within sentences and across sections of the report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629977Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3402-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A section about one feature of the report's subject contains specific facts and information to keep the reader engaged."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629982Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3402-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writers choose varied fronted adverbials and different sentence types to ensure the text flows for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629987Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3402-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sentences should be said aloud before writing to ensure they make sense and read back once written to check for errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629992Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7677-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of a conclusion is to summarise the key points in a text, providing closure to the subject."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.629996Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7677-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A summary sentence is the opening sentence of a conclusion and summarises the key points in a text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630001Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7677-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A conclusion begins with a formal fronted adverbial."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630008Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7677-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are no new facts or information about the subject in the conclusion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630013Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7677-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A conclusion finishes with the writer suggesting to the reader how to find out more about the subject."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630018Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6118-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is a critical part of the writing process."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630154Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6118-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing is most successful when editing is used to rethink, rephrase and reconsider first ideas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630159Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6118-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing can be done by oneself, with a peer or with a teacher."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630164Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6118-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Editing is most successful when it is chunked by punctuation, sentence structure, vocabulary and cohesive devices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6118-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A growth mindset helps us benefit most from editing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630173Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5498-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A comma is an important punctuation mark with more than one purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630205Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5498-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adding extra information to a clause is called parenthesis."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5498-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Parenthesis can be punctuated in a variety of ways."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630214Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5496-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A word family is a group of words common in feature, pattern or meaning. Prefixes and suffixes can build word families."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630219Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5496-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A synonym is a word with the same or similar meaning to another word and an antonym has the opposite meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630223Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5496-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A pronoun is a word that we use in place of a noun to avoid repetition."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630230Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5496-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A possessive pronoun is a type of pronoun that denotes possession of a noun by another noun."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630238Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5496-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A preposition is a word that connects a sentence to a noun or noun phrase to show where/when/why something's happening."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630243Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2747-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe is an important piece of punctuation with more than one purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630247Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2747-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can contract two words together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630252Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2747-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can show if a noun belongs to another singular noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630257Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2747-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can show if a noun belongs to another plural noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630261Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2747-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Contractions are useful in writing to indicate a character's informal speech."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630266Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6520-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when it is planned."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630271Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6520-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Understanding the question is critical to a successful essay answer."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630275Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6520-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An essay can use a bank of research, evidence and statistics to convince the reader of a certain viewpoint."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630280Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6520-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A structure that supports the line of argument must be logical."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630285Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7664-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making changes to improve our writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630289Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7664-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To edit punctuation, missing or incorrectly used capital letters, full stops, inverted commas and commas are checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630294Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7664-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When editing language, choices of words and phrases are carefully reviewed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630299Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7664-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Knowledge of synonyms is helpful to ensure vocabulary choices match their intended effect on the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630303Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7664-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing sentence structure, the way sentences are constructed is checked to improve and enhance text flow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630308Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6757-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A journalistic report has a formal tone and it combines factual statements with different perspectives on an event."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630312Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6757-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The main paragraphs give different perspectives, using both direct and reported speech."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630319Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6757-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The conclusion includes the 'official' perspective, gives the most up-to-date information and looks to the future."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630324Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6757-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Throughout, a range of cohesive devices can be used to connect ideas together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630329Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8072-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Back to Me’ can be considered a list poem; it contains 15 lines, with between 1-4 words in each."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630413Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8072-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Readers might connect to their thoughts, feelings and sense of identity in similar or different ways."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630418Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8072-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘Find Me’ is a fixed verse poem, split into 12 two-line verses."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630423Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8072-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A technique that poets can use to draw attention to specific lines is by changing the rhythm of the poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630428Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8072-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Friend' and 'Everyone' are poems by Laura Mucha."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630432Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7680-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Presenting involves speaking in front of others and listening to others."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7680-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Presenting involves speaking with clear diction and suitable volume, making eye contact and using strong body language."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630876Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7680-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Practising pronouncing tricky words helps develop clear diction when presenting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7680-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing helps the presenter to speak more confidently and fluently."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630886Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7680-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Pauses at the end of sentences can help the audience follow what is being said."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630890Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5626-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A diary entry recounts experiences chronologically and expresses emotions, thoughts and feelings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630895Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5626-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Exaggeration is often used to convey emotions in a diary entry."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630900Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5626-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Superlatives are used to compare one noun to an entire group of nouns, placing it at a higher degree."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5626-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Hyperbole is the use of exaggerated statements or claims."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630909Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5626-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A plan for a diary entry should include precise and ambitious vocabulary, including exaggeration."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630914Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4861-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes should not be written in full sentences and bullet points can be used to order notes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630918Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4861-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the paragraph is to explain about King Tut becoming king and what he achieved when in power."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4861-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Viewpoint fronted adverbials and formal fronted adverbials are used at the start of sentences for cohesion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630931Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4861-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A subheading signals part of a a text and should stand out from the rest of the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4861-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The plan should include subject-specific vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630943Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8069-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘I Opened the Door’ is inspired by another poem."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630948Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8069-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When a poem is heavily influenced by another poem, it's acknowledged with the word 'after' and the original poet's name."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630953Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8069-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The poem that inspired ‘I Opened the Door’ is called ‘A Poison Tree’, which was written by William Blake."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630958Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8069-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can compare and contrast poems based on many different aspects."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630962Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6117-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A conclusion is the final paragraph of a non-fiction text that gives general information about the subject."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630967Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6117-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A conclusion still has a subheading and an introductory sentence and it uses a range of cohesive devices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630972Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6117-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Before we write, we should orally rehearse sentences to ensure our sentences make sense and flow well."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630978Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6117-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we have finished our first draft of our writing, we edit it to improve and refine it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630983Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6117-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Editing includes looking at sentence structures, vocabulary, cohesive devices, spelling and punctuation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630988Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8877-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In Chapter 2 of ‘The Iron Man’, a character named Hogarth is introduced and he encounters the Iron Man."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630993Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8877-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Iron Man is responsible for eating the farmers’ machinery which threatens their livelihood and sense of safety."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.630998Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8877-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Humanity’s response to the Iron Man is one of anger and the farmers develop a plan to trap and bury him."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631002Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8877-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can infer deeper emotions of fear and confusion beneath humanity’s angry response."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631007Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8877-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Hogarth’s emotions shift to sorrow & guilt after the Iron Man is buried as he feels a sense of empathy & responsibility."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631012Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1063-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A subheading signals to the reader what the section is about."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1063-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A section about one feature of the report's subject contains specific facts and information to keep the reader engaged."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631024Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1063-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writers choose varied fronted adverbials and different sentence types to ensure the text flows for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631029Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1063-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A section can be composed of one paragraph."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631034Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1063-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sentences should be said aloud before writing to ensure they make sense and read back once written to check for errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631039Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7635-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Precise and ambitious vocabulary related to the five senses should be included in the plan."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631043Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7635-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Linguistic devices such as figurative language (similes and personification) should be included in the plan."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631048Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7635-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The plan should be written in note-form and notes are not written in full sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631053Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7635-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'zoom-in' structure guides the descriptive writing paragraph."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631058Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8071-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Forest' and 'The Colours of My Dreams' both have themes of belonging and hope."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631062Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8071-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Forest’ is a winter poem which focuses on themes of hope and belonging for a group of travellers making a journey."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631067Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8071-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The poem ‘The Colours of My Dreams’ includes vivid imagery linked to the five senses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631072Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8071-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Poetry is open to interpretation; it does not always offer answers."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631077Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3407-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making changes to improve writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3407-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing punctuation, missing or incorrect punctuation, like capital letters, full stops and commas, is checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631631Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3407-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing sentence structure, the flow of sentences and the variety of sentence types used are checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631636Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3407-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing language, word and phrase choices are checked to ensure they meet the tone required."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631641Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7641-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Exaggeration is a key feature of persuasive adverts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631646Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7641-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Comparatives and superlatives are techniques used to exaggerate and persuade."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631650Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7641-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Comparatives are used to compare two or more things."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631655Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7641-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Superlatives are used to compare one noun to an entire group of nouns, placing it at a higher degree."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631660Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7641-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Comparatives and superlatives are formed using suffixes or the words 'more' and 'most' to adapt adjectives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631665Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4859-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "King Tut was nine years old when he began ruling Egypt 3000 years ago."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631669Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4859-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "King Tut changed the religion of Ancient Egypt when he ruled."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4859-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """King Tut died aged 19 after ruling for 10 years. He was mummified so his body was preserved for 3000 years."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4859-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The archaeologist Howard Carter discovered his body surrounded by artefacts in 1922."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631684Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4859-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Two unborn mummified babies were found in the tomb so King Tut never passed the throne to his family."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631688Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6278-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Crazy About Cats’ provides information about different species of cats which can be compared and contrasted."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631693Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6278-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Non-fiction can develop curiosity by engaging readers' interests and encouraging a deeper exploration of topics."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631698Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6278-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Readers can ask questions of the text and illustrations to engage more fully with the information they have read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631705Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5756-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making changes to improve our writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631710Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5756-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing can be done by oneself, with a peer or with a teacher."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631714Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5756-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing punctuation, missing or incorrectly used capital letters, full stops and commas are all checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631719Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5756-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing sentence structure, the way sentences are constructed is checked to improve and enhance text flow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631724Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5756-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When editing language, choices of words and phrases are carefully reviewed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5492-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Any complex sentence is formed of at least one main clause joined to at least one subordinate clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631733Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5492-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are different types of subordinate clause: adverbial clause, relative clause and non-finite clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631738Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5492-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Any subordinate clause is a group of words that contains a verb and does not make complete sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631743Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5492-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are three types of complex sentence: adverbial, relative and non-finite."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5492-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are comma rules associated with clause demarcation in complex sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631752Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8640-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making changes to improve writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631757Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8640-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The job of an editor is to check punctuation and to make improvements to sentence structure and language choices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631761Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8640-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing punctuation, missing or incorrectly used capital letters, full stops and commas are checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631766Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8640-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing sentence structure, changes to the way sentences are constructed to improve text flow are made."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631771Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8640-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing vocabulary, reviews of word and phrase choice are made to ensure appropriate tone is achieved."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631775Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1107-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Relentless is an adjective which means constant or non-stop."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1107-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Scorching is an adjective which means red-hot or blazing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631787Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1107-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Suffocating is an adjective which means stuffy and smothering."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631795Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6276-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Non-fiction texts can be written using formal or informal language"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6276-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The language used in a text will depend on the text's purpose and audience"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6276-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Owen Davey uses subject specific language to help create a sense of authority and reliability for the reader"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631945Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6276-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Specific words and phrases can be selected by the author to convey meaning"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631950Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6276-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Owen Davey uses playful language to engage the reader"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.631954Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4811-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A prefix is a letter or group of letters added to the start of a word to change its meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632251Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4811-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The words start with a lead in and finish with a lead out."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632256Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4811-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The pencil does not lift when forming the join, only after to add the cross to a t or a dot to an i or a j."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632260Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4811-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are four cursive joins."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632268Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4811-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The join used depends on which letter is joining to which letter within a letter string."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632273Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7657-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Whale Rider' tells the story of Paikea and the challenges she faces and overcomes as a young girl in a Maori tribe."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632277Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7657-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A narrative can be structured into four key sections: the opening, the build-up, the climax and the resolution."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632282Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7657-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each part of a narrative has a specific purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632289Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7657-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can use our voice, language choices and expression to retell a story effectively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632294Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7657-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When retelling a story, it is important to convey the appropriate tone at each point of the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.632299Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5468-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea, topic or message that recurs in a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633008Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5468-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Anansi folktales explore themes relating to character in order to teach an important moral or lesson."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633013Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5468-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Anansi and the Antelope Baby' explores themes such as trickery, kindness, strength and loyalty."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633017Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5468-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Exploring themes can help us infer greater meaning from a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633022Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5468-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Anansi and Antelope use their strength in different ways to show one another kindness and protection."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633026Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6738-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when it is planned."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633758Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6738-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can plan to describe particular details and use figurative language to build a particular mood."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633763Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6738-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Our plan will cover two events from the build-up of 'A Kind of Spark', using a tense, anxious mood."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633770Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6738-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """For each event, we will describe it in the third person and reflect on it using internal monologue in the first person."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633775Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5662-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Beowulf arrives at Heorot, the Danish court, and he explains his plan to defeat Grendel to King Hrothgar."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633782Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5662-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """One Dane, Unferth, confronts Beowulf and says that he stands no chance against Grendel."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633787Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5662-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We are given the impression that Beowulf is very confident and that Unferth is very rude."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633794Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5662-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can find evidence within the text to support these impressions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633799Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5662-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Authors may consciously create impressions by dropping hints in a text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633804Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8094-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can develop our personal response to a text by reflecting on what we have read so far."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8094-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When giving a personal response, we can focus on emotional impact, characters, narrative elements, atmosphere & setting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8094-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """One of the prominent themes in the text is survival; it follows a family as they struggle to survive during a civil war."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633818Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8094-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Take-away ideas within a graphic novel may link to themes that are explored and developed in it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633823Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8634-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘The Borrowers’ is a fantasy fiction text written by Mary Norton in 1952."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633828Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8634-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Borrowers’ is about miniature people, who secretly live under the floorboards of an English house."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633832Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8634-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The protagonist in ‘The Borrowers’ is Arrietty, who is the daughter of Pod and Homily."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633837Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8634-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important for stories to have a clear structure so that readers can understand and enjoy them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.633842Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6275-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of a non-fiction text is to inform, explain, or provide factual information about a particular topic/subject"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634140Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6275-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are several features that non-fiction texts have in common."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634145Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6275-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An index in a non-fiction text allows readers to quickly locate specific topics, terms, or concepts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634149Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6732-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when structure, content and vocabulary are planned."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634355Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6732-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We aim to use a range of narrative elements in our writing and to set an appropriate mood with them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634360Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6732-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We use a range of cohesive devices to connect ideas, including a variety of fronted adverbials."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634365Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6732-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Short sentences, rhetorical questions and 'quick' fronted adverbials of time can add pace to a piece of writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634370Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6732-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Dashes can add dramatic effect, often by restating the noun phrase that is being described in a different way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634375Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4830-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing at speed is a valuable skill to develop."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634379Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4830-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing at speed can decrease the legibility and accuracy of your writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634384Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4830-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Regular practice, hand exercises and taking breaks can help to improve the speed and accuracy of your handwriting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634389Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4830-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When you are confident to write, you can increase the speed that you take notes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634394Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4830-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Note-taking can improve your learning experience."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634399Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6098-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Information can be gathered from a range of different sources."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634451Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6098-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Credibility of each source must be determined."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634456Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6098-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Origin of a source must be cited."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6098-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Full sentences are not required when writing in note form."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6098-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Notes can be organised by theme using bullet points."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634476Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6116-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Information in a section becomes more specific and detailed as the section goes on."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634530Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6116-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Facts written in a section should be researched and organised prior to writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634535Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6116-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A range of cohesive devices helps us to link facts within and between sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634539Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6116-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Before we write, we should orally rehearse sentences to ensure our sentences make sense and flow well."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634544Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6116-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Parenthesis, varied sentence types and a range of fronted adverbials are all cohesive devices that can be used."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634548Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28983-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The City of my birth' is a poem written by Karl Nova, published in his 2017 collection 'Rhythm and Poetry'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634553Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28983-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Imagery refers to the use of language that evokes vivid pictures in the reader's mind."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634558Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28983-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In the poem, Nova uses visual language to paint a vivid picture of London for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634562Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28983-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The atmosphere that Nova creates is one of a busy, energetic and joyful city."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634567Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28983-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Nova's poetry is influenced by hip-hop culture and it has a natural rhythm and flow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634572Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-9041-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The Adventure of the Blue Carbuncle' is a Sherlock Holmes short story first published in 1892."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634576Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-9041-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The story is told in the first person from the perspective of Dr John Watson."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634581Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-9041-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When you deduce something, you are arriving at a conclusion by logical reasoning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634586Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-9041-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """One of Holmes' key character traits is his ability to deduce information from small clues."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634590Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8474-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the climax is to describe the main action and take the suspense to its highest point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634643Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8474-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In the climax, the Iron Man resurfaces from the earth and Hogarth persuades the farmers not to harm him."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634648Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8474-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Precise and ambitious vocabulary, as well as ‘show and tell’, help take the suspense to its highest point in the climax."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634653Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8474-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Direct speech is used to convey Hogarth’s intentions to the Iron Man."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634658Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8474-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A plan includes notes, a sequence of events and ambitious vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634662Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8879-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In Chapter 4 of ‘The Iron Man’, the world faces threat from a flying creature named the space-bat-angel-dragon."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634667Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8879-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In Chapter 5 of ‘The Iron Man’, the Iron Man defeats the space-bat-angel-dragon and protects the Earth."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634672Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8879-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A character arc is a character’s transformation or journey over the course of a story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8879-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can examine the Iron Man’s character arc by considering how he is viewed by others over the course of the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634684Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8879-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Iron Man’s character evolves from one that is feared into one that is understood and viewed as a hero."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634689Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2740-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The verb carries the tense of a sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634723Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2740-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The progressive tense can denote present, past or future action."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2740-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The progressive tense is a tense that makes use of an auxiliary verb from the infinitive 'to be' with the main verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634733Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2740-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The progressive tense denotes ongoing action."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634738Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2740-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The main verb in the progressive tense always ends with the -ing suffix."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634742Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7669-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of a resolution is to resolve the story and give the reader a chance to reflect."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7669-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using the full range of sentence types (simple, compound and complex) improves text flow and cohesion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634752Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7669-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of time, place and manner describe the action in the main clause in further detail."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634756Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7669-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Oral rehearsal before writing helps to structure grammatically correct sentences and check for sense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.634761Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6279-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Crazy About Cats’ encourages various connections: text-to-self, text-to-text, and text-to-world."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635050Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6279-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Through real-world connections, non-fiction texts can inspire positive actions and change in readers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635055Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6279-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Readers can summarise main ideas of non-fiction texts by returning to the contents page to reflect on their reading."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635059Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6279-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Owen Davey uses a range of formal and informal language to engage the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635064Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6279-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Readers can focus on a number of features of the text to consider its purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635071Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7915-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'A Kind of Spark' is a novel set in Scotland and written by Elle McNicoll, who is autistic herself."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635177Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7915-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Addie, the main protagonist, is autistic, but this does not define her exclusively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635182Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7915-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The book is written in the first person from Addie's perspective."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635187Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7915-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When we read, we make inferences about characters based on evidence in the text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7915-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """At the start of the book, Addie has a close relationship with her sister Keedie - but not with her sister Nina."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635199Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4806-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635204Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4806-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The words start with a lead in and finish with a lead out."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635208Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4806-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The pencil does not lift when forming the join, only after to add the cross to a t or a dot to an i or a j."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635213Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4806-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are four cursive joins."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635218Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4806-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The join used depends on which letter is joining to which letter within a letter string."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635223Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7877-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Princess Sophia Duleep Singh: My Story’ is a historical fiction text set between 1886-1928."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635227Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7877-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sophia's life was intertwined with significant events related to the British Empire's rule over India."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635232Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7877-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The text explores British history as well as celebrating diversity, with strong themes of family & justice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635237Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5495-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A grammatically accurate sentence has a subject and a verb. It can contain an object."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635242Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5495-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A sentence can be written or spoken in the active voice."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635246Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5495-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A sentence can be written or spoken in the passive voice."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635251Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5495-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The active voice and passive voice are useful for different purposes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635256Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8635-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The opening introduces the Clock family as the main characters and describes the setting of their home."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635260Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8635-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Clock family live under the kitchen floorboards and access the upstairs through a hole at the bottom of a clock."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635265Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8635-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Clock family’s home is made up of items borrowed from the human “beans”, which are used in new ways."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635272Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8635-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A character trait is a special quality that makes a character in a story unique or interesting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635277Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8635-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can infer different character traits of Pod, Homily and Arrietty through exploring their experiences and actions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635284Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2726-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making changes to improve our writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635291Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2726-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing can be done by oneself, with a peer or with a teacher."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635296Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2726-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing punctuation, missing or incorrectly used capital letters, full stops, inverted commas & commas are checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635301Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2726-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing sentence structure, the way sentences are constructed is checked to improve and enhance text flow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635306Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2726-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When editing language, choices of words and phrases are carefully reviewed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635311Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28403-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """At the end of the text, Nate leaves primary school with his friends around him & Dylan has been released from hospital."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635629Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28403-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The theme of identity is conveyed through Nate’s emotional journey to find out who he is."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635633Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28403-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Hearing from the author and illustrator can enhance the reading process by adding layers of meaning and context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635638Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28403-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A take-away idea within a text may link to themes that are explored and developed in it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635643Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28403-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We will all have different ideas and responses to a text as we are all unique."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635647Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6277-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Readers can use layout features of a non-fiction text to navigate sections quickly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635655Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6277-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Skimming and scanning is a strategy readers can use to retrieve the information they are looking for rapidly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6277-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The structure and features of a text can help identify keywords or key information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635664Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6736-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The events culminating in the meeting between Miss Murphy and Addie's sisters are a key part of the build-up."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635692Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6736-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we write these events, we will need to understand the characters' actions and feelings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635697Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6736-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use drama to help us understand and remember these actions and feelings."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635702Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6736-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We will also want to use internal monologue to show Addie's inner thoughts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635707Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6736-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can practise saying these inner thoughts using drama."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635712Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1318-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A plan includes keywords and subject-specific vocabulary related to the section."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635716Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1318-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Taking notes is a skill."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635721Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1318-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes should not be written in full sentences and bullet points can be used to order notes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635726Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1318-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Key vocabulary and linguistic devices should be logged in a plan."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635730Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1318-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The plan should be clearly structured in the order of the section."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635735Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1317-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A subheading signals to the reader what the section is about."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635742Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1317-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Careful selection of nouns and pronouns ensures cohesion within sentences and across sections of the report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1317-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A section about one feature of the report's subject contains specific facts and information to keep the reader engaged."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635752Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1317-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writers choose varied fronted adverbials and different sentence types to ensure the text flows for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635757Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1317-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sentences should be said aloud before writing to ensure they make sense and read back once written to check for errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635761Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6346-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A text gives us clues about a character's features and feelings."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635769Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6346-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Some text clues about a character are explicit and some text clues about a character use subtext."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635774Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6346-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can infer a character's traits by examining their behaviour."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635779Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6346-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sherlock Holmes is a complex character."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635783Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6346-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Shrewd', 'unflappable', 'presumptuous' and 'assertive' are words that can be used to describe Sherlock Holmes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635790Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6352-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when it is planned."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635803Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6352-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The paragraph should give a reason, followed by evidence to support that reason."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6352-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We should include a range of persuasive techniques in the paragraph."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6352-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Within the paragraph, ideas are connected using cohesive devices."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635819Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6352-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Parenthesis can be added to clarify a noun using commas or to emphasise a point using dashes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635823Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8808-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A range of skills are involved in presenting to ensure that the audience are engaged and understand you."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635828Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8808-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Building suspense for the audience is the main purpose when presenting a section of a narrative build-up."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635833Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8808-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Eye contact, projection and diction are important for ensuring the audience can hear and understand you."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635838Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8808-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Pace, body language and tone are crucial for conveying the atmosphere and a character’s emotions in a narrative."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635845Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8808-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Pace, body language and tone can be altered in different ways to support the building of suspense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.635850Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8070-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The Wall' uses symbolism - the use of objects, images, or actions that represent ideas beyond their literal meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636232Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8070-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The wall in the poem can represent a physical isolation as well as an emotional one."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636237Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8070-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A poem can have several meanings and interpretations; each person’s response can be different and unique to them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636242Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8070-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can respond to a poem by writing a personal response to it."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636247Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7673-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The plan includes keywords and subject-specific vocabulary related to the section."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636292Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7673-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Taking notes is a skill."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636300Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7673-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes should not be written in full sentences and bullet points can be used to order notes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636305Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7673-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Key vocabulary and linguistic devices should be logged in a plan."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636738Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7673-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The plan should be clearly structured in the order of the section."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636746Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7922-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In this section of the book, we see Joseph subjected to bullying."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636790Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7922-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adonis intervenes, putting Bert at risk; Joseph helps Bert escape, but he is not thanked for this."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636794Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7922-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can compare character experiences across a book, identifying a character's lows and highs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636799Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7922-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can try and spot connections between different characters and their experiences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636804Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7922-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "These connections might be intended by the author or not."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.636809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1315-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An introduction's purpose is to give general facts to the reader and to encourage them to read on."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637053Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1315-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The introduction gives general facts about the unique characteristics of the anglerfish."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637058Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1315-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The introduction tells the reader what they will learn in the rest of the report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637062Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4831-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Pen and pencil are the most common tools used to write or draw with."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637067Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4831-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Making a choice between pen and pencil depends on the task and the desired outcome."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637072Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4831-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using a pencil allows for mistakes to be corrected easily with an eraser, which is ideal for sketching and drafting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637076Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4831-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using a pen is ideal for final drafts as pen is permanent and looks neat and professional."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637081Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4831-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Over time you will develop a personal preference for using pen or pencil."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637086Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6347-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can imagine Sherlock Holmes receiving lots of letters from potential clients asking him to help."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637091Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6347-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can imagine Holmes would only take on interesting cases, perhaps from people in desperate need."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637098Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6347-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A letter to Holmes would have been formal in tone, given his position in society."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637103Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6347-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A persuasive letter contains elements of both persuasion and explanation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637108Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6347-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The explanation must be coherent and a range of persuasive devices can be used."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637113Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6413-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Caribbean immigrants were drawn to the UK by the promise of better pay and living conditions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637117Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6413-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Windrush arrivals were given some support by the British government, but they faced discrimination."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637122Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6413-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It could be hard to find housing and many could only find jobs at a lower level than they were qualified for."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637126Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6413-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The weather and appearance of Britain was also a shock to some of the Windrush immigrants."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637131Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6413-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Nevertheless, many stayed in Britain and their descendants live here to this day."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637136Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6740-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We are writing about an event from the build-up, using a third person perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637265Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6740-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We are then using internal monologue to reflect on the same event from Addie's perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637270Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6740-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using a plan and orally rehearsing our writing helps us to do our best writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637275Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6740-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We should aim to use a complete range of sentence types and language features in our writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637282Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6416-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when we orally rehearse before writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637301Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6416-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A diary can include events and feelings written in the past and present tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637309Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6416-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We use a range of cohesive devices in all writing, including different punctuation, sentence types and parenthesis."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637314Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6416-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Because a diary is a personal piece of writing, it can have a conversational tone."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637319Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6416-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can create a conversational tone using questions, exclamatives, verbless sentences and conversational openers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637324Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5457-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theme is a big idea, topic or message that recurs within a story and authors use these to convey deeper meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637381Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5457-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Identifying the themes within ‘The Moon Dragons’ helps us understand the deeper meaning behind the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637385Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5457-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Themes are often communicated through exploring negative and positive character traits."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637390Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5457-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Key themes such as bravery, protection and morality are conveyed through Alina’s admirable character traits."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637395Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5457-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The themes within ‘The Moon Dragons’ help us consider the complexities of human morality."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637399Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4827-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Direct speech is signalled to the reader in text by inverted commas."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637404Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4827-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Direct speech can be written in a speech first sentence or a speech second sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637409Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4827-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Direct speech always starts with a capital letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637413Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4827-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """After forming a capital letter, you need to lift your pencil to start the next part of the word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637418Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4827-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The writing is legible and the letter sizing is consistent."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.637423Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7676-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A subheading signals to the reader what the section is about."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638158Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7676-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Careful selection of nouns and pronouns ensures cohesion within sentences and across sections of the report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638162Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7676-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A section about one feature of the report's subject contains specific facts and information to keep the reader engaged."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638167Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7676-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writers choose varied fronted adverbials and different sentence types to ensure the text flows for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638172Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7676-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sentences should be said aloud before writing to ensure they make sense and read back once written to check for errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638177Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3405-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of a conclusion is to summarise the key points in a text, providing closure to the subject."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638181Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3405-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A summary sentence is the opening sentence of a conclusion and summarises the key points in a text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638189Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3405-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A conclusion begins with a formal fronted adverbial."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638194Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3405-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are no new facts or information about the subject in the conclusion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638199Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3405-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A conclusion finishes with the writer suggesting to the reader how to find out more about the subject."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638203Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6341-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sir Arthur Conan Doyle wrote the ’Sherlock Holmes’ stories starting in 1886."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638869Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6341-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Sherlock Holmes' was written in the Victorian Era."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638876Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6341-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Victorian city of London was a city of startling contrast between rich and poor."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6341-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The Holmes stories are written in the first person from Watson's perspective."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638889Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6726-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing our storytelling using a text map makes the writing process easier."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638917Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6726-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can also plan some of the vocabulary we wish to use to have a certain effect."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638922Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6726-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We are going to be writing the build-up of 'Beowulf and the dragon'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638927Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6726-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can use rich vocabulary to describe the burned stronghold, the rocky headland and the dragon's body."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638932Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6726-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can avoid repeating 'Beowulf' and 'the dragon' by replacing them with varied noun phrases."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7679-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making changes to improve writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638941Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7679-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing punctuation, missing or incorrect punctuation, like capital letters, full stops and commas, is checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638946Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7679-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing sentence structure, the flow of sentences and the variety of sentence types used are checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638951Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7679-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing language, word and phrase choices are checked to ensure they meet the tone required."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638955Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7927-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Coming to England' is an autobiographical memoir, written by Floella Benjamin."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638960Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7927-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Floella writes about her early childhood in Trinidad in an overwhelmingly positive tone."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638965Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7927-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Floella has good relationships with both her parents; she describes them through actions that they perform."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638969Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7927-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Floella has five siblings: Sandra, Lester, Ellington, Roy and Cynthia."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638976Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6353-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when structure, content and vocabulary are planned."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638981Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6353-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The conclusion should use a range of persuasive techniques to drive home the point of the letter."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638986Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6353-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Within the paragraph, ideas are connected using cohesive devices."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638991Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6353-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A formal letter finishes with a sign-off from the writer."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.638998Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8473-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In part two of the build-up, humanity responds angrily to the Iron Man by trapping and burying him."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639027Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8473-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There is a contrast between how the farmers and Hogarth feel after the Iron Man is buried."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639031Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8473-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The use of precise and ambitious vocabulary supports the building of suspense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639036Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8473-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Show and tell’ can be used to convey emotions and how these intensify and shift."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639040Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8473-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using a range of sentence types supports text flow and helps achieve the text’s purpose."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639045Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7632-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A simile  describes something by comparing it to something else to make the description more vivid."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639050Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7632-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Personification gives human characteristics to something non-human."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639055Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7632-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using a variety of sentence types in descriptive writing engages the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639059Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1105-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Searing' is an adjective which means burning or scorching."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639116Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1105-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Stifling' is an adjective which means smothering or suffocating."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1105-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Sweltering' is an adjective which means very hot or baking."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639128Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6765-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Presenting involves speaking in front of others and listening to others."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639662Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6765-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Presenting includes voice projection, speaking with clear diction, making eye contact and using strong body language."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639669Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6765-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Voice projection is not the same as shouting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6765-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Practising pronouncing tricky words helps develop clear diction when presenting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.639682Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6724-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Beowulf was written by Anglo-Saxons in England about events in Scandinavia."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640123Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6724-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The story refers to some historical figures, but lots of the story is fictional."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640128Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6724-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In Anglo-Saxon society, warriors were highly respected. We can see evidence of this in 'Beowulf'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640132Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6724-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The overall story focuses on the 'problem' of Beowulf's quest for fame."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640137Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6724-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The story is made up of three mini-stories, each with their own story structure."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640142Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5486-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Skimming and scanning are crucial skills when it comes to quickly retrieving information from texts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640147Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5486-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Readers can infer by using clues from within the text to draw conclusions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640154Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5486-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Evidence from the text can be used to develop answers to questions and support reasoning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640159Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8897-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Characterisation is the way an author describes and develops the personalities and traits of the characters in a story"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640163Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8897-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Characterisation can be understood by looking at actions, thoughts, dialogue and characters' interactions with others"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8897-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reader's Theatre is an activity where participants read aloud from a script to convey part of a story to an audience"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640173Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8897-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reader’s Theatre is a really enjoyable way to read a text aloud and can help develop fluency when reading"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640177Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1068-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of a conclusion is to summarise the information of the text for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640182Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1068-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A summary sentence summarises the key information from the text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1068-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A conclusion can begin with a formal fronted adverbial."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640199Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1068-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "No new information about the subject is given to the reader in the conclusion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640204Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1068-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A conclusion finishes with the writer suggesting to the reader how to find out more."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5817-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Viewer’ is a narrative fiction story with elements of mystery and supernatural fantasy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640214Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5817-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The setting in the opening is a ‘dump’ in the city."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640218Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5817-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The story features a magical object that is found at the dump."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640223Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5817-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The distinctive illustrations play an important part in telling the story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640228Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5817-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The story ends in an unusual and mysterious way."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640232Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6751-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing is most successful when the structure, content and vocabulary are planned."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640874Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6751-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can plan precise vocabulary to include in our narrative to contribute to a fast, threatening mood."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640879Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6751-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we plan the content of our writing, we combine this vocabulary with actions and descriptive and emotive details."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640884Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7908-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘London is the Place for Me’ was written by Aldwyn ‘Lord Kitchener’ Roberts in 1948."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640889Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7908-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To better understand the song and its lyrics, we can explore the context in which it was written."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640896Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7908-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Roberts migrated to the UK aboard the Empire Windrush; his arrival coincided with a period of significant change."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640901Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7908-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The first two stanzas were sung by Lord Kitchener at the Tilsbury docks, on board the HMT Empire Windrush."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640906Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7908-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Roberts’ experiences were not the same for all people who migrated from the Caribbean."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640911Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5750-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are five main food groups in a balanced diet: protein, fats, carbohydrates, dairy and fruit and vegetables."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640916Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5750-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Humans should aim to eat 30 plant-based foods a week."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640920Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5750-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """All the food groups need to be eaten in moderation to maintain a healthy, balanced diet."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640927Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5750-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Exercise is an essential factor towards leading a healthy lifestyle."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640934Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5750-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sleep is essential for good health."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640939Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4862-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A subheading signals to the reader what the section is about."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640946Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4862-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A section about one feature of the report's subject contains specific facts and information to keep the reader engaged."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640952Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4862-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using the full range of sentence types (simple, compound and complex) improves text flow for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640956Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4862-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sentences should be said aloud before writing to ensure they make sense and read back once written to check for errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640961Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4862-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of cause and formal fronted adverbials are used at the start of sentences for cohesion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640966Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6745-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We are writing a narrative that includes switches in perspective and tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.640997Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6745-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In this lesson, we will write only a present tense, first person paragraph in role as Addie."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641002Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6745-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Because we are in role as Addie, we may use some informal language features like short sentences and contractions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641007Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6745-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We will also want to include the full range of sentence structures and punctuation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641012Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6745-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Orally rehearsing our writing helps us to be prepared to write."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6760-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Information can be gathered from a range of different sources."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641118Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6760-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The Prophet Muhammad was the founding prophet of Islam."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641123Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6760-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Early Islamic civilisation emerged in the 7th century CE."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641127Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6760-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Early Islamic civilisation had and still has a profound effect on many areas of society across the world."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641132Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6760-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Understanding the chronology of a time period enables us to understand it in greater depth."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641137Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4832-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The quotation is demarcated with inverted commas."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641142Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4832-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The quotation starts with a capital letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641146Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4832-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """After forming a capital letter, you need to lift your pencil to start the next part of the word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641151Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4832-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letter spacing and letter sizing is consistent so the writing is legible."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641156Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4832-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A range of joins will be used depending on which letters are joining to which letters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641160Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8898-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Hiccup’s character goes on a transformation throughout the text; he begins the text as an unlikely hero"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641165Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8898-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Hiccup’s characterisation does not remain fixed; by the end of the text he demonstrates many heroic qualities"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641170Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8898-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea, topic or message that recurs within a story"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641174Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8898-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Themes can leave us with ideas and questions that we reflect on after reading the text"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641179Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3455-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are different tenses and ways of forming verbs in English."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641184Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3455-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In the passive voice, the verb is 'done to' the subject."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641188Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3455-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The passive voice allows the speaker or writer to sound more detached from the sentence content than the active voice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641193Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3455-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The active voice is the most frequently heard, spoken and written voice in English."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641197Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3455-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A clause in the passive voice contains two verbs: an auxiliary verb from the infinitive 'to be' and the past participle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641205Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7920-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'When the Sky Falls' is set in 1941, during the Second World War."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7920-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A 12-year-old boy, Joseph Palmer, is sent from rural Yorkshire to the city."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641214Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7920-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Joseph finds himself in the care of Margaret Farrelly (Mrs F)."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641221Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7920-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The narrative has historical details that are interwoven into the fictional narrative."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641226Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7920-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Joseph and Mrs F are both characterised as hostile or cold initially."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641231Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6102-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A non-chronological report is written to inform the reader about a subject or event out of time order."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641790Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6102-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The introduction of a non-chronological report summarises the general information about the subject."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641795Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6102-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Within the introduction, text that flows well and cohesively is important."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641800Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6102-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Text cohesion can be achieved by using a range of cohesive devices."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641805Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6102-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can use compound sentences, complex sentences, fronted adverbials and parenthesis as cohesive devices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3468-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Activity outside the hive is an important part of the honey-making process."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3468-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The main sections in an explanation text follow a clear, sequenced order."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641819Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3468-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes should not be written in full sentences and bullet points can be used to make notes clear."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641823Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3468-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Facts become increasingly specific throughout one section of an explanation text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641829Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7931-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘Coming to England’ highlights Floella’s resilience and advocacy against racism."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641836Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7931-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The text has themes of determination, migration, identity and overcoming adversity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641841Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7931-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Floella has a strong support network; she describes positive traits that she has learnt from both her parents."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641846Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7931-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea, topic or message that recurs within a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641850Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6161-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can present our written work in a range of ways, including orally."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641855Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6161-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A radio broadcast will usually be briefer and slightly less formal than a written journalistic report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641859Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6161-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It may still include statements of fact and reported speech that give different perspectives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641864Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6161-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instead of direct speech, we will hear individuals' accounts as interview segments."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641869Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6161-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We will use some language specific to radio broadcasts, such as 'correspondent' and 'studio'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.641873Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7672-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An introduction's purpose is to give general facts to the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642044Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7672-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The introduction gives general facts about the time period and origins of the Ancient Greeks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642048Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7672-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The introduction tells the reader what they will learn in the rest of the report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642053Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5661-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Beowulf' is an epic poem set in Denmark and Sweden during the 500s CE and written in England in around 1000 CE."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642058Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5661-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The story follows the heroic deeds of the warrior Beowulf. It was written in Old English by an unknown author."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642067Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5661-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In translation, the text still includes archaic language due to its historical context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642072Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5661-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Beowulf, a Geat, volunteers to travel to Denmark to defeat Grendel, a monster who has been terrorising the Danes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642077Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5661-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The author makes specific language choices in order to give us particular impressions of characters and events."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642081Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4812-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Silent letters are letters that are not pronounced when the word is spoken."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642086Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4812-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Practising writing words with silent letters in cursive can improve your handwriting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642090Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4812-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The words start with a lead in and finish with a lead out."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642095Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4812-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are four cursive joins; which is used depends on which letter is joining to which letter within a letter string."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642100Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4812-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You do not lift your pencil when forming the joins."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642104Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4833-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing with emphasis involves making certain words or phrases stand out."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4833-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing with emphasis  helps to show what’s most important or exciting in the writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642114Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4833-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are different strategies to show emphasis in your writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642118Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4833-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Capital letters, underlining or repeating a word or phrase can emphasise importance or express excitement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642123Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4833-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adding an exclamation mark can emphasise strong emotions to the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642128Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5472-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading between the lines to search for clues can help to infer meaning."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642132Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5472-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Evidence from the text helps us to justify our inferences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642139Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5472-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Asking questions provides an opportunity to deepen our understanding of a text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642144Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8477-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In the resolution, the Iron Man finds a new home in a metal scrapyard and he no longer needs the farmers’ machinery."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642198Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8477-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Exaggeration is a key part of conveying positive emotions in the resolution of a narrative."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642203Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8477-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Superlative adjectives and similes are used to exaggerate and build imagery for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642207Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8477-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Superlatives are used to compare one noun to an entire group of nouns, placing it at a higher degree."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642212Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8477-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A simile is a linguistic device that compares two things using ‘like’ or ‘as’, highlighting similarities."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642217Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5820-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the opening is to provide the reader with a detailed description of the setting and main character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5820-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Literary devices that create figurative language include metaphors, similes and personification."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642229Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5820-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A metaphor is a type of figurative language that involves describing something as though it actually is something else."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642233Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5455-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Alina’s motivations for finding the moon dragon was different to everyone else’s and she valued them more than gold."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642571Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5455-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Asking questions and having rich discussions builds our understanding and allows us to hear different perspectives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642575Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5455-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Searching for clues within a text can help us infer greater meaning."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642580Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5455-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can retrieve evidence from the text to help us justify our inferences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642585Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5455-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A character's actions, experiences and words can be analysed to infer greater meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642590Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8880-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Iron Man goes from being feared due to his difference, to being understood, accepted and ultimately admired."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642594Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8880-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theme is a big idea, topic or message that recurs within a story and authors use these to convey deeper meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642599Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8880-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Considering the deeper meaning behind the Iron Man’s story can help us identify themes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642606Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8880-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Key themes such as difference, perception and understanding are explored through the Iron Man’s character arc."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642611Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8880-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The themes within ‘The Iron Man’ help us learn important lessons about issues and topics in our own lives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642616Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7653-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Direct speech is punctuated using inverted commas. Dialogue moves the action forward."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642623Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7653-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Notes from a plan are used to form full sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642628Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7653-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A range of sentence types (simple, compound and complex) improves text flow for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642632Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7653-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A range of fronted adverbials is used to improve text flow."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642637Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7653-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the climax is to describe the main action and to take the tension and excitement to its highest point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642642Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5751-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The purpose of the introduction is to give general information to the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642647Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5751-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The introduction outlines what the reader will learn from the non-chronological report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642651Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5751-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The facts in the opening are general about healthy lifestyle; they become more specific in later paragraphs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642656Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5751-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An introduction ends with a command to the reader to continue reading."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642661Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5751-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A compound sentence is formed of two main clauses joined with a co-ordinating conjunction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642668Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4816-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A haiku is a short poem of just three lines."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642673Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4816-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each line of the poem starts on a new line and with a capital letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642678Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4816-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """After forming a capital letter, you need to lift your pencil to start the next part of the word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.642683Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4816-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Each letter string contains different letter joins depending on which letters are in the word."""@en ;
