  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A relative complex sentence uses a relative pronoun (who or which) to provide greater detail about a noun."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694309Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7349-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Inverted commas are used to demarcate speech and a piece of punctuation separates speech from the reporting clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694313Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2706-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe is an important piece of punctuation with more than one purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694318Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2706-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can contract two words together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694322Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2706-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can show if a noun belongs to another singular noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694327Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2706-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can show if a noun belongs to another plural noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694331Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2706-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Apostrophes for contraction and possession are useful in writing for different reasons."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694335Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1381-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When adding suffixes to words ending in ‘fer’, the ‘r’ is doubled if the –fer is still stressed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694362Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1381-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The ‘r’ is not doubled if the ‘fer’ is no longer stressed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694367Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1381-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can use a range of strategies to practise spellings and help embed them in our memory."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694371Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1381-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the curriculum words: purpose and suppose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694376Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1380-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When adding suffixes to words ending ‘fer’, the ‘r’ is doubled if the 'fer' is still stressed when the ending is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694383Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1380-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The ‘r’ is not doubled if the ‘fer’ is no longer stressed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694388Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1380-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can use word maps to link related words and identify connections in the meaning and spelling of words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694392Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1380-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the curriculum words: sincere and sincerely."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694397Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1387-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are many ways to spell the ‘ee’ sound, including ‘ee’, ‘ea’, ‘e-e’, ‘e’, ‘y’, ‘ey’, ‘ie’ and ‘ei’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694401Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1387-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The rule ‘i before e except after c’ can help choose between ‘ie’ and ‘ei’ when spelling ‘ee’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694406Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1387-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The letter string ‘ei’ can represent a range of different sounds, including ‘ay’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694411Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1387-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the curriculum words: height, eighth and foreign."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694417Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1453-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A homonym is a word which has the same spelling but multiple meanings."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694441Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1453-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The meaning of a homonym is dependent on the context."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694445Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1453-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using the strategy 'pyramid letters' is a useful practice strategy."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1453-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the curriculum word: surprise."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694456Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1360-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In words of French origin, the 'sh' sound is generally spelt 'ch', the 'g' sound is 'gue' and the 'k' sound is 'que'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694461Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1360-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In words of Latin origin, the 's' sound is generally spelt 'sc'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694466Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1360-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In words of Greek origin, the 'k' sound is generally spelt 'ch' and the 'f' sound is 'ph'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694472Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1360-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the curriculum words: interfere, signature."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6009-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A written argument tries to convince the reader of something using strong reasoning to support."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694725Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6009-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The PEPS structure stands for: point, explanation, proof, summary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694730Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6009-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Formal fronted adverbials are formal in tone and link one sentence to the previous sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694734Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6009-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A fronted adverbial of cause is a sentence starter that tells the reader the cause and effect of something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694739Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1034-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A subheading signals to the reader what the section is about."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694743Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1034-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A section about one feature of the report's subject contains specific facts and information to keep the reader engaged."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694748Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1034-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writers choose varied fronted adverbials and different sentence types to ensure the text flows for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694752Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1034-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A section can be composed of one paragraph."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694757Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1034-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sentences should be said aloud before writing to ensure they make sense and read back once written to check for errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694763Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1362-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the word ends in a consonant, generally just add the suffix -ed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694849Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1362-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the word ends in 'y', remove the 'y' and add -ied."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694854Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1362-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the word ends in 'e', remove the 'e' and add -ed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694858Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1362-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If there is a short vowel sound, double the consonant and add -ed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694863Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1362-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """How to spell a range of curriculum words, including equip, equipped and attached."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1372-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the word ends in a consonant, generally just add "-tion"; this is the best bet for the "shun" sound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694872Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1372-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the word ends in \"t\", remove the \"t\" and add \"-tion\"."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694878Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1372-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the word ends in \"te\", remove the \"te\" and add \"-tion\"."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694884Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1372-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the word ends in \"e\" or \"y\", remove the \"e\" or \"y\" and add \"-ition\"."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694888Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-1372-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the curriculum words: competition, mention and position."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694893Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6728-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """As we write, we aim to include a range of narrative elements and to connect ideas using a range of cohesive devices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695654Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6728-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A range of types of complex sentence - adverbial, relative and non-finite (-ing) - can be used as cohesive devices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6728-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Colons and semi-colons are also useful cohesive devices."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695663Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6728-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can orally rehearse our ideas prior to writing in order to make it easier when we come to write."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695668Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4858-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A non-chronological report is a non-fiction text providing information about a particular subject."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695672Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4858-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A non-chronological report can be organised into an introduction, paragraphs organised by theme and a conclusion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4858-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Vocabulary within a non-chronological report is subject-specific and factual; the language and tone is formal."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695683Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4858-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Conjunctions are an important linguistic feature within non-chronological reports in order to ensure cohesion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695688Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4858-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials  are an important linguistic feature within non-chronological reports in order to ensure cohesion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695693Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6097-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Text cohesion refers to how a text flows together to maintain the interest of the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696158Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6097-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can improve text cohesion using cohesive devices that connect information within and between sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696162Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6097-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Compound and complex sentences can be used to join linked information in one sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696167Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6097-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials can be used to show links between information in adjacent sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696171Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6097-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are different types of complex sentence and fronted adverbials, which serve different purposes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696176Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6113-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Parenthesis can be achieved with a range of punctuation, including brackets and commas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696180Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6113-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Any type of parenthesis is additional information that can be removed without compromising grammatical accuracy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696185Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6113-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Brackets are useful in non-fiction writing to add extra, factual information."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696189Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6113-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Commas can demarcate a relative clause that is inserted into a sentence as parenthesis."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696194Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6113-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Commas are also useful to drop information into a clause."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696198Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5494-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The verb carries the tense of a clause."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696203Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5494-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The perfect tense uses auxiliary verbs based on 'to have' and a past tense form of the main verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696208Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5488-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Escape from Pompeii’ builds tension as the story progresses, drawing readers into the narrative of the eruption."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696403Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5488-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Tension can be built up in many ways thorough hinting, pacing, illustration, character reactions and cliffhangers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696407Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5488-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A turning point in a narrative is a pivotal moment that significantly alters the course of the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696412Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5488-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Turning points can evoke a range of emotions in the character."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696416Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5471-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can form judgements about characters and learn morals based on the actions and events in the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696421Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5471-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The story of 'Hansel and Gretel' is an example of how good triumphs over evil in fairytales."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696425Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5471-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Hansel and Gretel' contains many of the features of fairytales."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696430Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6101-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Parenthesis can be achieved with a range of punctuation, including brackets and commas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696434Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6101-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Any type of parenthesis is additional information that can be removed without compromising grammatical accuracy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696441Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6101-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Brackets are useful in non-fiction writing to add extra, factual information."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696446Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6101-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Commas can demarcate a relative clause that is inserted into a sentence as parenthesis."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696451Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6101-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Commas are also useful to drop information into a clause."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696455Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8469-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the opening is to engage the reader and to introduce the setting and characters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696460Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8469-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we plan, we note precise and ambitious vocabulary to help paint vivid pictures and convey the desired atmosphere."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696464Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8469-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A fronted adverbial of time, place or manner indicates when, where or how action in the rest of a sentence takes place."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696469Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8469-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A plan includes notes, a sequence of events and ambitious vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696473Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5818-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A setting is where or when a story takes place."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696478Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5818-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Atmosphere involves how a writer constructs their writing to convey emotions and mood to the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696484Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5818-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The atmosphere in the setting of ‘The Viewer’ is eerie, mysterious and tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696489Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5818-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Personification involves describing objects as if they are people and have feelings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696494Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5818-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use expanded noun phrases to add detail and description to a noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696498Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5821-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The opening is the first section of a story where the writer describes the setting and main characters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696503Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5821-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The opening should be descriptive and use figurative language to build an atmosphere for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5821-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A non-finite complex sentence contains a non-finite clause."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696512Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5821-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A non-finite clause extends the sentence by telling the reader about a second thing that the subject is doing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696517Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5821-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A non-finite clause can vary its position in a sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696521Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2741-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The verb carries the tense of a sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2741-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The perfect tense can denote present, past or future action."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696533Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2741-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The perfect tense is a tense that makes use of an auxiliary verb from the infinitive 'to have' with the main verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696538Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2741-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The auxiliary verb is followed by the past participle of the main verb in the perfect tense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696542Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7633-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Descriptive and ambitious vocabulary related to the five senses can be included in the plan."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696547Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7633-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Linguistic devices such as figurative language (similes and personification) should be planned."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696551Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7633-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Notes are used in planning and they are not written in full sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696556Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7633-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'zoom-in' structure guides the descriptive writing paragraph."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696560Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7926-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When reflecting on a text, we can consider characterss thoughts, feelings and actions and relate them to our own."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696565Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7926-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Omar’s strong bond with his brother is one of the core relationships in ‘When Stars are Scattered’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696571Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7926-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Throughout the text, Omar picks up on the inequality between what life is like for boys and girls at Dadaab."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696576Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7926-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The way that one reader connects with a text might be different to another based on their own life experiences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696581Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6741-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is a critical part of the writing process."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696831Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6741-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing is most successful when editing is used to rethink, rephrase and reconsider first ideas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696840Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6741-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing can be done by oneself, with a peer or with a teacher."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696845Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6741-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Editing is most successful when it is chunked by punctuation, sentence structure, cohesive devices and vocabulary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696850Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6741-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A growth mindset helps us benefit most from editing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696854Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4835-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Print handwriting is recommended for tasks where clarity, legibility and uniformity are essential."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696859Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4835-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Application forms and medical forms will require you to fill information out in print or block capitals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696863Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4835-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """E-mail addresses and postal addresses require the use of print letters or capital letters to ensure legibility."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4835-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Block capitals refer to the writing style where each letter is written as a capital letter and formed separately."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696872Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4835-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Letter formation and letter spacing should be accurate when writing in print to ensure legibility."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696876Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3471-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The steps in the honey-making process are written in chronological order."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3471-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Ordering fronted adverbials indicate the order of the steps in a process."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696885Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3471-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of cause explain the cause and effect of a fact across two sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696890Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3471-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using the full range of sentence types (simple, compound and complex) improves text flow for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696894Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3471-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Explanation texts include subject-specific vocabulary that is related to the subject of the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696901Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5752-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes should not be written in full sentences and bullet points can be used to order notes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696906Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5752-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the paragraph is to explain what food should be eaten to form a balanced diet."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5752-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of cause and formal fronted adverbials are used at the start of sentences for cohesion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696915Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5752-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A subheading signals part of a a text and should stand out from the rest of the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696921Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5752-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The plan should include subject-specific vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696926Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28984-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The City of my birth' is a poem that was written by Karl Nova in 2017 and it is influenced by hip-hop culture."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696931Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28984-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The atmosphere that the poem creates is one of a busy, energetic and joyful city."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696935Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28984-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There is a natural rhythm and flow throughout the poem."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696939Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28984-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Making notes on the poem about which words to emphasise can help a performer get ready to perform the poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696944Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28984-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Practising the poem ahead of time helps to improve a performance."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696948Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2719-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The conclusion of an explanation text summarises the information that has been provided."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696953Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2719-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The conclusion of an explanation text reviews the most important information using subject-specific vocabulary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696957Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2719-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The conclusion of an explanation text is an opportunity to encourage the reader to discover more about the subject."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696961Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2719-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using a range of simple, compound and complex sentences supports text flow."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696966Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-2719-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The use of compound and complex sentences are very effective for summarising."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696970Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6753-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing is most successful when structure, content and vocabulary is planned."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696975Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6753-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our climax should have a tense, fast-paced mood."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6753-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can combine descriptive details and emotive details to paint a clear picture for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696984Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6753-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can use a range of linguistic techniques and cohesive devices for increasing the pace."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6753-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We use precise vocabulary to add to the impression of speed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.696993Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7678-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making changes to improve writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697181Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7678-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing punctuation, missing or incorrect punctuation, like capital letters, full stops and commas, is checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697185Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7678-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing sentence structure, the flow of sentences and the variety of sentence types used are checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697190Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7678-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When editing language, word and phrase choices are checked to ensure they meet the tone required."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697194Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6730-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing is most successful when its structure, content and vocabulary are planned."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697199Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6730-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is also useful to orally rehearse storytelling the events we're going to write."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697204Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6730-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We will need to include rich vocabulary to show the action in the battle between Beowulf and the dragon."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697210Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-6730-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We will also need rich vocabulary to show the emotions Beowulf and Wiglaf experience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697215Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8027-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reader identity is the process of reflecting on what you enjoy or do not enjoy reading"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697220Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8027-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading can take many forms; it does not have to be restricted to a book"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8027-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading is a skill that you use every single day"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697229Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-8027-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A reading preference can include what we read and where we read."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697233Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5490-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are four types of noun: common, proper, collective and abstract."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697285Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5490-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Nouns, verbs, adjectives and adverbs build clauses."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697290Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5490-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Determiners introduce nouns."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697297Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-5490-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Modal verbs are a type of auxiliary verb."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697302Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4829-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Information in a non-chronological report is organised using a title, subheadings and paragraphs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697431Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4829-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The subheadings start with a capital letter and are underlined."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697436Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4829-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The capital letter does not join to the next letter in the letter string."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4829-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The joins used depend on which letter is joining to which letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697445Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4829-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The letter formation and letter spacing is accurate to ensure the writing is legible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4800-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Cursive handwriting involves joining letters together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697454Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4800-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letters all have a lead in starting at the baseline."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4800-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The first join goes from the baseline to the x-height line."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4800-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The pencil does not lift when forming the join."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697469Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-4800-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letter w lead out \"finishes with a small dip down\" to aid joining."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697476Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3467-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An explanation text needs a title to signify what the text is about."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697481Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3467-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of an introduction is to hook the reader in and inform the reader what the rest of the text will be about."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697488Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3467-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The introduction contains general facts, an outline of what the text will cover and a direct appeal to the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697492Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-3467-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Facts and information in the introduction are general; they become more specific and detailed in later paragraphs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.697497Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

